data.enText: a climbing plant that produces grapes

data.chText: 藤本植物；攀缘植物；藤；藤蔓
data.enText: any climbing plant with long thin stems ; one of these stems

tr: a plant with a weak stem that derives support from climbing, twining, or creeping along a surface

value.def: A vine is a plant that grows up or over things, especially one which produces grapes.

example.ex: Every square metre of soil was used, mainly for olives, vines, and almonds.
example.tran: 每一寸土地都利用上了，主要用来种植橄榄树、葡萄藤和杏树。

value.tran: 藤本植物;攀援植物;（尤指）葡萄藤

trans: 依赖男子的妇女；依赖男子的女人；绝对不会是狗皮膏药；爬藤
葡萄藤；葡萄藤舞步；葡萄树
